From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ArcBoost Builder <build@arcboost.local>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 22:15:11 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 10/13] ArcBoost: reject circular_feature on GPU/CUDA device
 types
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The GPU and CUDA tree learners maintain their own histogram and split-finding
kernels that haven't been extended for arc-search. Rather than silently
producing inconsistent splits or crashing inside the device kernel, validate
at config-load time and Log::Fatal with a message that points at the right
fix (use device_type='cpu' or drop circular_feature).

The CLI binary build is already auto-disabled in v4.6.0 when __BUILD_FOR_PYTHON
is set (CMakeLists.txt lines 62-64), so the 'strip CLI' goal from the plan
needs no additional patch. The R-package directory is independent of the
main CMake target and ships separately upstream — also nothing to do.

This rounds out the v0 patch series at 10 commits ready for git format-patch.
---
 src/io/config.cpp | 13 +++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/io/config.cpp b/src/io/config.cpp
index 3f8e85d1..a1cb0866 100644
--- a/src/io/config.cpp
+++ b/src/io/config.cpp
@@ -415,6 +415,19 @@ void Config::CheckParamConflict(const std::unordered_map<std::string, std::strin
       Log::Warning("Although \"deterministic\" is set, the results ran by GPU may be non-deterministic.");
     }
   }
+  // ArcBoost: circular features require the CPU SerialTreeLearner path. The
+  // GPU and CUDA tree learners have their own histogram/split-finder kernels
+  // that haven't been extended for arc-search. Reject early with a clear
+  // message rather than silently producing wrong splits or crashing inside
+  // the device kernels.
+  if (!circular_feature.empty()
+      && (device_type == std::string("gpu") || device_type == std::string("cuda"))) {
+    Log::Fatal(
+        "ArcBoost: circular_feature is not supported on device_type='%s' in "
+        "v0.1.0.dev0. Set device_type='cpu' (default) or remove circular_feature "
+        "to use the GPU/CUDA path with categorical/numerical handling.",
+        device_type.c_str());
+  }
   // linear tree learner must be serial type and run on CPU device
   if (linear_tree) {
     if (device_type != std::string("cpu") && device_type != std::string("gpu")) {
